Jacques Celliers is the Chief Executive Officer of First National Bank – a position he has held since 2017. Celliers studied at Stellenbosch University, and also received an MBA from the University of Cape Town Graduate School of Business. As FNB CEO, he has recently been focused on steering FNB and its customers through a tough economic climate and is excited about the future of banking in a post-pandemic South Africa. In this Episode of Business Talk, Celliers discusses how FNB has adapted to support its clients’ evolving needs and interests. He also explains how he expects the banking industry will continue to evolve once the pandemic is truly behind us. Celliers talks about the exciting awards FNB has recently won – including Best SME Bank in South Africa and Africa at the Global SME Finance Awards, and Most Valuable Brand in the annual Kantar BrandZ rankings. He unpacks why FNB deserved to win these titles and explains why this recognition is so important. Celliers also discusses FNB’s focus on innovation, touching on two of FNB’s newest SME solutions – FNB WebStore and FNB Android Speedpoint device. He then identifies his key theme for the banking industry in 2022, and concludes by discussing FNB’s future plans for 2022 and beyond. Click here to learn more about Monocle Solutions 